{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So I'm going to tell you a little bit"},{"time":2000,"text":"about reimagining food."},{"time":4000,"text":"I've been interested in food for a long time."},{"time":6000,"text":"I taught myself to cook"},{"time":8000,"text":"with a bunch of big books like this."},{"time":10000,"text":"I went to chef school in France."},{"time":13000,"text":"And there is a way"},{"time":15000,"text":"the world both envisions food,"},{"time":17000,"text":"the way the world writes about food and learns about food."},{"time":20000,"text":"And it's largely what you would find in these books."},{"time":23000,"text":"And it's a wonderful thing."},{"time":25000,"text":"But there's some things that have been going on"},{"time":27000,"text":"since this idea of food was established."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"In the last 20 years,"},{"time":32000,"text":"people have realized that science"},{"time":34000,"text":"has a tremendous amount to do with food."},{"time":36000,"text":"In fact, understanding why cooking works"},{"time":39000,"text":"requires knowing the science of cooking --"},{"time":41000,"text":"some of the chemistry, some of the physics and so forth."},{"time":44000,"text":"But that's not in any of those books."},{"time":46000,"text":"There's also a tremendous number of techniques"},{"time":48000,"text":"that chefs have developed,"},{"time":50000,"text":"some about new aesthetics, new approaches to food."},{"time":53000,"text":"There's a chef in Spain named Ferran Adria."},{"time":56000,"text":"He's developed a very avant-garde cuisine."},{"time":58000,"text":"A guy in England called Heston Blumenthal,"},{"time":61000,"text":"he's developed his avant-garde cuisine."},{"time":63000,"text":"None of the techniques that these people have developed"},{"time":65000,"text":"over the course of the last 20 years"},{"time":67000,"text":"is in any of those books."},{"time":69000,"text":"None of them are taught in cooking schools."},{"time":71000,"text":"In order to learn them, you have to go work in those restaurants."},{"time":74000,"text":"And finally,"},{"time":76000,"text":"there's the old way of viewing food"},{"time":78000,"text":"is the old way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80000,"text":"And so a few years ago -- fours years ago, actually --"},{"time":83000,"text":"I set out to say, is there a way"},{"time":85000,"text":"we can communicate science and technique and wonder?"},{"time":89000,"text":"Is there a way we can show people food"},{"time":91000,"text":"in a way they have not seen it before?"},{"time":93000,"text":"So we tried, and I'll show you what we came up with."},{"time":96000,"text":"This is a picture called a cutaway."},{"time":99000,"text":"This is actually the first picture I took in the book."},{"time":101000,"text":"The idea here is to explain what happens"},{"time":103000,"text":"when you steam broccoli."},{"time":105000,"text":"And this magic view allows you to see"},{"time":107000,"text":"all of what's happening"},{"time":109000,"text":"while the broccoli steams."},{"time":111000,"text":"Then each of the different little pieces around it"},{"time":113000,"text":"explain some fact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"And the hope was two-fold."},{"time":117000,"text":"One is you can actually explain what happens when you steam broccoli."},{"time":119000,"text":"But the other thing is that maybe we could seduce people"},{"time":122000,"text":"into stuff that was a little more technical,"},{"time":124000,"text":"maybe a little bit more scientific, maybe a little bit more chef-y"},{"time":127000,"text":"than they otherwise would have."},{"time":129000,"text":"Because with that beautiful photo,"},{"time":131000,"text":"maybe I can also package this little box here"},{"time":133000,"text":"that talks about how steaming and boiling"},{"time":135000,"text":"actually take different amounts of time."},{"time":137000,"text":"Steaming ought to be faster."},{"time":139000,"text":"It turns out it isn't because of something called film condensation,"},{"time":142000,"text":"and this explains that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144000,"text":"Well, that first cutaway picture worked,"},{"time":147000,"text":"so we said, \"Okay, let's do some more.\""},{"time":150000,"text":"So here's another one."},{"time":152000,"text":"We discovered why woks are the shape they are."},{"time":155000,"text":"This shaped wok doesn't work very well;"},{"time":157000,"text":"this caught fire three times."},{"time":159000,"text":"But we had a philosophy,"},{"time":161000,"text":"which is it only has to look good for a thousandth of a second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"And one of our canning cutaways."},{"time":168000,"text":"Once you start cutting things in half, you kind of get carried away,"},{"time":171000,"text":"so you see we cut the jars in half as well as the pan."},{"time":174000,"text":"And each of these text blocks"},{"time":176000,"text":"explains a key thing that's going on."},{"time":178000,"text":"In this case, boiling water canning"},{"time":181000,"text":"is for canning things that are already pretty acidic."},{"time":183000,"text":"You don't have to heat them up as hot"},{"time":185000,"text":"as you would something you do pressure canning"},{"time":188000,"text":"because bacterial spores can't grow in the acid."},{"time":192000,"text":"So this is great for pickled vegetables,"},{"time":194000,"text":"which is what we're canning here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196000,"text":"Here's our hamburger cutaway."},{"time":198000,"text":"One of our philosophies in the book"},{"time":200000,"text":"is that no dish"},{"time":202000,"text":"is really intrinsically any better than any other dish."},{"time":204000,"text":"So you can lavish"},{"time":206000,"text":"all the same care, all the same technique,"},{"time":209000,"text":"on a hamburger"},{"time":211000,"text":"as you would on some much more fancy dish."},{"time":213000,"text":"And if you do lavish as much technique as possible,"},{"time":216000,"text":"and you try to make the highest quality hamburger,"},{"time":218000,"text":"it gets to be a little bit involved."},{"time":220000,"text":"The New York Times ran a piece"},{"time":222000,"text":"after my book was delayed"},{"time":224000,"text":"and it was called \"The Wait for the 30-Hour Hamburger"},{"time":227000,"text":"Just Got Longer.\""},{"time":229000,"text":"Because our hamburger recipe, our ultimate hamburger recipe,"},{"time":232000,"text":"if you make the buns and you marinate the meat and you do all this stuff,"},{"time":235000,"text":"it does take about 30 hours."},{"time":237000,"text":"Of course, you're not actually working the whole time."},{"time":239000,"text":"Most of the time is kind of sitting there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"The point of this cutaway"},{"time":243000,"text":"is to show people a view of hamburgers they haven't seen before"},{"time":245000,"text":"and to explain the physics of hamburgers"},{"time":247000,"text":"and the chemistry of hamburgers,"},{"time":249000,"text":"because, believe it or not, there is something to the physics and chemistry --"},{"time":252000,"text":"in particular, those flames underneath the burger."},{"time":255000,"text":"Most of the characteristic char-grilled taste"},{"time":258000,"text":"doesn't come from the wood or the charcoal."},{"time":261000,"text":"Buying mesquite charcoal will not actually make that much difference."},{"time":264000,"text":"Mostly it comes from fat pyrolyzing, or burning."},{"time":267000,"text":"So it's the fat that drips down and flares up"},{"time":270000,"text":"that causes the characteristic taste."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"Now you might wonder, how do we make these cutaways?"},{"time":274000,"text":"Most people assume we use Photoshop."},{"time":276000,"text":"And the answer is: no, not really;"},{"time":278000,"text":"we use a machine shop."},{"time":281000,"text":"And it turns out, the best way to cut things in half"},{"time":284000,"text":"is to actually cut them in half."},{"time":287000,"text":"So we have two halves of one of the best kitchens in the world."},{"time":289000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":291000,"text":"We cut a $5,000 restaurant oven in half."},{"time":295000,"text":"The manufacturer said,"},{"time":297000,"text":"\"What would it take for you to cut one in half?\""},{"time":299000,"text":"I said, \"It would have to show up free.\""},{"time":301000,"text":"And so it showed up, we used it a little while,"},{"time":303000,"text":"we cut it in half."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"Now you can also see a little bit how we did some of these shots."},{"time":308000,"text":"We would glue a piece of Pyrex"},{"time":310000,"text":"or heat-resistant glass in front."},{"time":313000,"text":"We used a red, very high-temperature silicon to do that."},{"time":316000,"text":"The great thing is, when you cut something in half,"},{"time":318000,"text":"you have another half."},{"time":320000,"text":"So you photograph that in exactly the same position,"},{"time":322000,"text":"and then you can substitute in --"},{"time":324000,"text":"and that part does use Photoshop -- just the edges."},{"time":327000,"text":"So it's very much like in a Hollywood movie"},{"time":329000,"text":"where a guy flies through the air, supported by wires,"},{"time":331000,"text":"and then they take the wires away digitally"},{"time":333000,"text":"so you're flying through the air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335000,"text":"In most cases, though, there was no glass."},{"time":337000,"text":"Like for the hamburger, we just cut the damn barbecue."},{"time":340000,"text":"And so those coals that kept falling off the edge,"},{"time":343000,"text":"we kept having to put them back up."},{"time":345000,"text":"But again, it only has to work for a thousandth of a second."},{"time":347000,"text":"The wok shot caught fire three times."},{"time":350000,"text":"What happens when you have your wok cut in half"},{"time":352000,"text":"is the oil goes down into the fire"},{"time":354000,"text":"and whoosh!"},{"time":356000,"text":"One of our cooks lost his eyebrows that way."},{"time":358000,"text":"But hey, they grow back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360000,"text":"In addition to cutaways,"},{"time":362000,"text":"we also explain physics."},{"time":364000,"text":"This is Fourier's law of heat conduction."},{"time":366000,"text":"It's a partial differential equation."},{"time":368000,"text":"We have the only cookbook in the world"},{"time":370000,"text":"that has partial differential equations in it."},{"time":372000,"text":"But to make them palatable,"},{"time":374000,"text":"we cut it out of a steel plate and put it in front of a fire"},{"time":377000,"text":"and photographed it like this."},{"time":379000,"text":"We've got lots of little tidbits in the book."},{"time":382000,"text":"Everybody knows that your various appliances"},{"time":384000,"text":"have wattage, right?"},{"time":387000,"text":"But you probably don't know that much about James Watt."},{"time":389000,"text":"But now you will; we put a biography of James Watt in."},{"time":392000,"text":"It's a little couple paragraphs"},{"time":394000,"text":"to explain why we call that unit of heat the watt,"},{"time":397000,"text":"and where he got his inspiration."},{"time":399000,"text":"It turned out he was hired by a Scottish distillery"},{"time":402000,"text":"to understand why they were burning so damn much peat"},{"time":404000,"text":"to distill the whiskey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406000,"text":"We also did a lot of calculation."},{"time":408000,"text":"I personally wrote thousands of lines of code"},{"time":410000,"text":"to write this cookbook."},{"time":412000,"text":"Here's a calculation"},{"time":414000,"text":"that shows how the intensity of a barbecue,"},{"time":416000,"text":"or other radiant heat source, goes"},{"time":418000,"text":"as you move away from it."},{"time":420000,"text":"So as you move vertically away from this surface,"},{"time":422000,"text":"the heat falls off."},{"time":424000,"text":"As you move side to side, it moves off."},{"time":426000,"text":"That horn-shaped region"},{"time":428000,"text":"is what we call the sweet spot."},{"time":430000,"text":"That's the place where the heat is even to within 10 percent."},{"time":433000,"text":"So that's the place where you really want to cook."},{"time":435000,"text":"And it's got this funny horn-shaped thing,"},{"time":437000,"text":"which as far as I know, again,"},{"time":439000,"text":"the first cookbook to ever do this."},{"time":441000,"text":"Now it may also be the last cookbook that ever does it."},{"time":444000,"text":"You know, there's two ways"},{"time":446000,"text":"you can make a product."},{"time":448000,"text":"You can do lots of market research"},{"time":450000,"text":"and do focus groups"},{"time":452000,"text":"and figure out what people really want,"},{"time":454000,"text":"or you can just kind of go for it"},{"time":456000,"text":"and make the book you want and hope other people like it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"Here's a step-by-step that shows grinding hamburger."},{"time":462000,"text":"If you really want great hamburger,"},{"time":464000,"text":"it turns out it makes a difference if you align the grain."},{"time":467000,"text":"And it's really simple, as you can see here."},{"time":469000,"text":"As it comes out of the grinder, you just have a little tray,"},{"time":471000,"text":"and you just take it off in little passes,"},{"time":473000,"text":"build it up, slice it vertically."},{"time":475000,"text":"Here's the final hamburger."},{"time":477000,"text":"This is the 30-hour hamburger."},{"time":479000,"text":"We make every aspect of this burger."},{"time":481000,"text":"The lettuce has got liquid smoke infused into it."},{"time":484000,"text":"We also have things about how to make the bun."},{"time":487000,"text":"There's a mushroom, ketchup -- it goes on and on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490000,"text":"Now watch closely. This is popcorn. I'll explain it here."},{"time":493000,"text":"The popcorn is illustrating"},{"time":495000,"text":"a key thing in physics."},{"time":497000,"text":"Isn't that beautiful?"},{"time":499000,"text":"We have a very high-speed camera,"},{"time":502000,"text":"which we had lots of fun with on the book."},{"time":504000,"text":"The key physics principle here"},{"time":506000,"text":"is when water boils to steam"},{"time":508000,"text":"it expands by a factor of 1,600."},{"time":510000,"text":"That's what's happening to the water inside that popcorn."},{"time":512000,"text":"So it's a great illustration of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"Now I'm going to close with a video that is kind of unusual."},{"time":517000,"text":"We have a chapter on gels."},{"time":519000,"text":"And because people watch Mythbusters and CSI,"},{"time":522000,"text":"I thought, well, let's put in a recipe"},{"time":524000,"text":"for a ballistics gelatin."},{"time":527000,"text":"Well, if you have a high-speed camera,"},{"time":529000,"text":"and you have a block of ballistics gelatin lying around,"},{"time":532000,"text":"pretty soon somebody does this."},{"time":536000,"text":"(Gasps)"},{"time":538000,"text":"Now the amazing thing here"},{"time":540000,"text":"is that a ballistics gelatin is supposed to mimic"},{"time":542000,"text":"what happens to human flesh when you get shot -- that's why you shouldn't get shot."},{"time":545000,"text":"The other amazing thing is, when this ballistics gelatin comes down,"},{"time":548000,"text":"it falls back down as a nice block."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550000,"text":"Anyway, here's the book."},{"time":553000,"text":"Here it is."},{"time":557000,"text":"2,438 pages."},{"time":561000,"text":"And they're nice big pages too."},{"time":564000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":572000,"text":"A friend of mine complained"},{"time":574000,"text":"that this was too big and too pretty to go in the kitchen,"},{"time":576000,"text":"so there's a sixth volume"},{"time":578000,"text":"that has washable, waterproof paper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}